<div class="postright">
<h3>Re: Insane trouble with realtek wifi card</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<p>Hi,<br/>The simplest way is, assuming you have build-essential installed, and also blacklisted any other related driver, do: &quot;sudo apt install r8168-dkms&quot;.<br/>reboot, and relogin. have fun.</p><p>If does not work, get the driver you need from [http://www.realtek.com.tw/downloads/downloadsView.aspx?Langid=1&amp;PNid=13&amp;PFid=5&amp;Level=5&amp;Conn=4&amp;DownTypeID=3&amp;GetDown=false#2], unzip it and install &quot;sudo ./autorun.sh&quot;.</p>
<p class="postedit"><em>Last edited by gnugr (2017-03-29 16:42:24)</em></p>
</div>
<div class="postsignature postmsg"><hr/><p>GPG FINGERPRINT: 868D EF24 37CC E9F5 C5DC&#160; 63B7 5E57 25A1 FB41 2219<br/>GPG KEY: <a href="https://pgp.mit.edu/pks/lookup?op=vindex&amp;search=0x868DEF2437CCE9F5C5DC63B75E5725A1FB412219" rel="nofollow">https://pgp.mit.edu/pks/lookup?op=vinde … A1FB412219</a></p></div>
